b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe38268.htm)  [Next](sbe38270.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1417930330/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Vedanta Sutras of Badarayana, Commentary by Sankara (SBE38)_ , tr. by\nGeorge Thibaut [1896] at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\n8\\. And on account of thoughtfulness.\n\nMoreover also the word 'thoughtfulness' denotes a lengthened carrying on of\nthe same train of ideas. Now 'thoughtfulness' we ascribe to those whose mind\nis concentrated on one and the same object, while their look is fixed and\ntheir limbs move only very slightly. We say e.g. that the crane is thoughtful,\nor that a wife whose husband has gone on a journey is thoughtful. Now such\nthoughtfulness is easy for those who sit; and we therefore conclude herefrom\nalso that meditation is the occupation of a sitting person.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: IV, 1, 9](sbe38270.htm)\n\n"